        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 1:51PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 151 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 16 miles northwest of Lima, or 27 miles south of
Dillon, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lima, Dell, Bannack Pass, and Snowline.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
